<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08288</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROHIBITING THE DISPOSAL OF ELECTRONIC DEVICES AT SOLID WASTE MANAGEMENT FACILITIES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Refers “Electronic Device” to a desktop or laptop computer, computer monitor, portable computer, cathode ray tube, flat panel television, or cellular phones.

Intends to prohibit the disposal of any electronic device in mixed solid waste; and prohibit Solid Waste Management Facility to accept for disposal or incineration of any such device.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>VILLARICA, LINABELLE RUTH R.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-09-25</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Tambunting (000 2018-10-15)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON ECOLOGY ON 2018-09-25</td></tr></table>